t990.text: So here is to 2020. I want it to be a good one. And... I think I got this.

t991.text: There's been a lot glossed over (hobbies, cars, pets) but this was the important one to get out there. Those other things are inconsequential without a healthy head...

t992.text: I have managed to achieve a good understanding employer (Westwide, now Horizons West), which has improved my mental health enormously on its own. I finally feel this overly long period of mental mediocrity is over, I feel well again.

t993.text: Mum would not see my 2019, the year it all finally clicked into place. ASD diagnosed, stream changed, help from service provider stepped up. Max Employment got me to the next step, Bizlink saw the transformation through.

t994.text: Got a mental health plan started. Saw a psychologist. Got on a path to see a clinical psychologist to finally have my Autistic Spectrum Disorder made official. I needed this to improve any chance of having a decent understanding employer.

t995.text: Despite this, I continued on, my depression and anger at how shit employers were to me regarding truth was getting to me. I was broken.

t996.text: I lost my best friend to cancer, his missus some time later. Little would I know but mum would also pass away before the new decade happened.

t997.text: The job disappeared, the friends group disintegrated a fair amount. It was the continuation of struggle with just getting by.
